definition: surname Yin/abbr. for 印度[Yin4 du4]
to print/to mark/to engrave/a seal/a print/a stamp/a mark/a trace/image

sentences.english: Some appear to have been attacked by the beaks of other cephalopods.
sentences.chinese: 有些牙印似乎是被其他頭足綱攻擊的痕跡。

sentences.english: Snakebite usually have no more than Yayin.
sentences.chinese: 無毒蛇咬傷通常有多個牙印。

sentences.english: When I was 4 years old, I sank my teeth into my parents' walnut dresser.
sentences.chinese: 當我四歲時，我把父母的胡桃木梳妝檯上咬上牙印。

sentences.english: Rather, my mother lovingly dusted my dental impressions for the next 40 years.
sentences.chinese: 相反，40年來母親充滿深情地將牙印上的灰塵擦去。

sentences.english: These could only have been made after the dinosaur was dead.
sentences.chinese: 這些深層牙印只有等恐龍死了時候纔有可能被留下。

sentences.english: This means a quick gnaw to real gold would actually leave an indentation.
sentences.chinese: 這就意味着迅速咬一下真正的黃金，會留下牙印。

sentences.english: I am boradcasting on the all AM frequences.
sentences.chinese: 我正在所有的鐵絲上留下牙印。
